"title": "8405: commands, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8405",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The NT sets out the commands of God and Jesus Christ for the church.</p>\n<h2>Commands made by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:36-Matt22:40\">MAT 22:36–22:40</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:28-Mark12:31\">MRK 12:28–12:31</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:3\">MAT 15:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:9\">MRK 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:8\">MRK 7:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:46-Acts13:47\">ACT 13:46–13:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:30\">ACT 17:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:32\">ROM 1:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:1\">1TI 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:3\">TIT 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:23\">1JN 3:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:21\">1JN 4:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:4\">2JN 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>Commands made by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>In the Gospels</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:34\">JHN 13:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:26-Matt8:27\">MAT 8:26–8:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:39-Mark4:41\">MRK 4:39–4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:24-Luke8:25\">LUK 8:24–8:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:25-Mark1:27\">MRK 1:25–1:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:35-Luke4:36\">LUK 4:35–4:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:43\">MRK 5:43</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:56\">LUK 8:56</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25\">MRK 9:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:12\">JHN 15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:17\">JHN 15:17</a></p>\n<h3>In the rest of the NT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:14\">1CO 9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:42\">ACT 10:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:10-1Cor7:11\">1CO 7:10–7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:37\">1CO 14:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:2\">1TH 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:2\">2PE 3:2</a> <em>“the command” (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:21\">2Pe 2:21</a>) here refers to Christianity considered as a body of ethical teaching</em></p>\n<h2>Commands made by the apostles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:7-1John2:8\">1JN 2:7–2:8</a></strong> <em>They received the command to love at the beginning of their Christian experience.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:48\">ACT 10:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:4\">ACT 16:4</a> <em>The Greek word translated “decisions” literally means “decrees”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:18\">ACT 16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:4\">2TH 3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:6\">2TH 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:11-2Thess3:121\">2TH 3:11–3:121</a>TI <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:3-2Thess1:5\">1:3–1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:11\">1TI 4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:17-1Tim6:18\">1TI 6:17–6:18</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:13-1Tim6:14\">1TI 6:13–6:14</a></p>\n<h2>Obedience to the NT commands</h2>\n<h3>Obedience is a requirement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:3-1John2:4\">1JN 2:3–2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:19\">MAT 5:19</a> <em>“these commandments” probably refers to the OT law as fulfilled by Jesus Christ (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17-Matt5:18\">Mt 5:17–18</a>)</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:17\">MAT 19:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:10\">LUK 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:10\">JHN 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:19\">1CO 7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:21\">2PE 2:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:21-1John3:24\">1JN 3:21–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:5-2John1:6\">2JN 1:5–1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:12\">REV 14:12</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience is an expression of love and faithfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:21\">JHN 14:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:15\">JHN 14:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:14\">JHN 15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:2-1John5:3\">1JN 5:2–5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:17\">REV 12:17</a></p>\n<h2>Commands given by secular authorities</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:9\">MAT 8:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:8\">LUK 7:8</a> <em>the Roman centurion</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:9-Matt14:10\">MAT 14:9–14:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:27\">MRK 6:27</a> <em>Herod orders the beheading of John the Baptist</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:64-Matt27:65\">MAT 27:64–27:65</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:1\">LUK 2:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:19\">ACT 12:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:22-Acts16:24\">ACT 16:22–16:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:2\">ACT 18:2</a> <em>Claudius ordered all the Jews to leave Rome</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:34\">ACT 21:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:10\">ACT 23:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:35\">ACT 23:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:6\">ACT 25:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:17\">ACT 25:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:21\">ACT 25:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:23\">ACT 25:23</a></p>\n<h2>Commands given by religious authorities</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:57\">JHN 11:57</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:15\">ACT 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:28\">ACT 5:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:40\">ACT 5:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:2-Acts23:3\">ACT 23:2–23:3</a></p>\n<h2>Commands that came through Moses referred to in the NT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:19-Heb9:20\">HEB 9:19–9:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:4\">MAT 8:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:44\">MRK 1:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:7-Matt19:8\">MAT 19:7–19:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:3-Mark10:4\">MRK 10:3–10:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:5\">JHN 8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:8-Rom7:13\">ROM 7:8–7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:18-Heb12:21\">HEB 12:18–12:21</a></p>",
